I had an amazing meal from @mexicodiner_ this afternoon! I found the restaurant on @grubhub which is also available on @seamless and @doordash Firstly it was delicious. The shrimp and the sauce it comes in is fantastic. The shrimp tacos was delicious and they provide homemade salsa verde 😋 it comes with rice and black beans. The shrimp taco was really good I love the fresh cilantro and lime to garnish it. The fish taco was good but my one thing to say is it could use a better quality fish inside. I would pay more for the taco to have that tender , melt in your mouth type of fish inside. Of course Chilean sea bass would be most ideal but to keep it at a certain price point I would consider Basa/Swai fish or Pollock those are more fluffy and retain more moisture. Other than that I loved every bite.

The neighborhood needed a top-notch Mexican restaurant and with Mexico Diner we've got just that! Everything I've ever ordered from here was fresh and homemade, brought to me quickly by a very friendly delivery guy. I love the chicken fajita because it's flavorful and lean. The chili relleno is absolutely delicious. They always give you a ton of hot, fresh corn tortillas. If you run out there's something seriously wrong with you. The rice and beans are highly addicting and so is their green salsa. That stuff makes the food taste even better and I don't know how that is even possible! And did I mention that prices are very reasonable?  This restaurant took a very long time to open. Construction seemed to move at the pace of a tired snail creeping against traffic on an airport people mover. I thought for sure it would be a disaster or a front for the mob but things turned out much better then I had expected. And now I have a new go-to Mexican restaurant that blows everything I've tried over the last 5 years living in the neighborhood out of the water.
